  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { Playground, PropsTable } from 'docz'
import Loadable from './'
import { Logo } from '../../atoms/'

export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"loadable-component"}}>{`Loadable component`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"basic-usage"}}>{`Basic usage`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`The Loadable component is a wrapper to waiting actions :) He uses the `}<MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`React Suspends`}</MDXTag>{` with a loading fallback`}</MDXTag>
